Bullets:
Institute a [public 401(k)](https://storage.googleapis.com/pfa-webapp/documents/PFA_Retirement_White_Paper.pdf) that 
• includes both a Rainy Day Account and a Retirement Account; 
• automatically triggers a 3 percent contribution from employer into the Retirement Account when a worker contributes 1.5 percent of pre-tax income into the Rainy Day Account; 
• waives penalties for any type of withdrawal from the Rainy Day Account and allows withdrawals from the Retirement Account for emergencies with the penalties either waived or reduced based on the person’s income; 
• exempts employers that currently offer a defined benefit pension, 401(k), or similar retirement plan from requirement to contribute to public 401(k); 
• initially requires large employers to contribute to public 401(k) plans with that requirement next extended to medium-sized employers and then eventually to small employers; and 
• limits maximum amount of contributions

