Expand the [earned income tax credit](https://www.mikebloomberg.com/policies/housing-and-earned-income-tax-credit-proposals) to 
• increase the credit, particularly for low-income workers who do not reside with children; 
• [lift the age cap](https://content.mikebloomberg.com/Retirement-Policy-Prose.pdf) for low-income workers who do not reside with children; 
• lower the income thresholds for receiving the maximum credit and make the credit available to more filers; 
• simplify the eligibility rules and make it easier for people to claim the credit; 
• pay the credit each month rather than once a year; 
• institute a pilot program that would extend eligibility to caregivers and other unpaid workers and others engaged in ineligible employment; and 
• institute another pilot program that would pay a [place-based credit in distressed communities](https://content.mikebloomberg.com/Mike-Bloomberg-2020-Agriculture-Policy.pdf)

